dev` - Check package version and details\n\n### Potential Solutions:\n1. **Install Different Package**: Look for `libsharpyuv-dev` or similar package (may not exist in Ubuntu 20.04).\n2. **Build WebP from Source**: Download and build newer WebP version with SharpYUV support.\n3. **Linker Flag Adjustment**: Use `-lwebp` instead of `-lsharpyuv` if symbols are in main WebP library.\n4. **Symbol Renaming**: Check if SharpYUV functions have different names in older WebP versions.\n5. **Disable Feature**: If possible, configure GDAL to not use SharpYUV features.\n\n### Common Pitfalls:\n1. **Version Mismatch**: GDAL may expect newer WebP API than available in Ubuntu 20.04.\n2. **Symbol Visibility**: SharpYUV symbols might be in `libwebp` but not exported with expected names.\n3. **Build Configuration**: GDAL\'s CMake configuration may need adjustment for older WebP versions.\n4. **Dependency Chain**: Other libraries (like poppler) may also have WebP dependencies causing conflicts.\n\n### Recommended Approach:\n1. First diagnose what WebP version is installed and what SharpYUV components exist.\n2. Check GDAL\'s CMake configuration for WebP/SharpYUV detection.\n3. Consider building WebP from source if missing functionality.\n4. As last resort, patch GDAL to not require SharpYUV or use alternative implementation.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 2] Partial progress: Resolved 3 out of 4 missing libraries (brotli, bz2). SharpYUV library still missing despite installing libwebp-dev. Need to investigate if sharpyuv is a separate component or requires different package/version. The webp library may need to be built from source or a newer version may be required.\n- [Attempt 1] Excellent progress: Build moved from network/download failure (original error) to successful compilation but linker failure. The GDAL library compiled 100% successfully (libgdal.a built). Current issue is missing system libraries (-lbrotlidec, -lbrotlicommon, -lsharpyuv, -lbz2) needed for fuzzer linking. This is a typical dependency issue that can be fixed by installing missing packages in the Docker container.\n- [Attempt 2] Partial progress: Resolved 3 out of 4 missing libraries (brotli, bz2). SharpYUV library still missing despite installing libwebp-dev. Need to investigate if sharpyuv is a separate component or requires different package/version. The webp library may need to be built from source or a newer version may be required. The Ubuntu 20.04 base image\'s libwebp-dev package (version 0.6.1) might not include SharpYUV support.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2016 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:0c229e61349e6e5f4dbcfd433b2b0b5906012d49216675a6402ad1ed270715c4\nRUN apt-get update && \\\n    apt-get install -y make autoconf automake libtool g++ curl cmake sqlite3 pkg-config \\\n    libbrotli-dev libbz2-dev libwebp-dev\n\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/OSGeo/gdal gdal\n\nRUN cp gdal/fuzzers/build.sh $SRC/\n\nWORKDIR gdal\n\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://gdal.org"\nlanguage: c++\nprimary_contact: "even.rouault@gmail.com"\nauto_ccs:\n  - "schwehr@gmail.com"\n  - "mateusz@loskot.net"\n  - "bishop.dev@gmail.com"\n  - "juergen.fischer@gmail.com"\n  - "athomas@thinkspatial.com.a